  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nHello! I am faced with an issue: I turn off one of my validators but `validator_monitor_prev_epoch_attestation_block_inclusions` still shows `1` value which means what beacon node see attestation from my validator in new blocks.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2993917/142390693-cc28e301-3e7d-4f34-a584-cd7515e5a6a9.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2993917/142390905-c07e1018-04d8-47be-9cc4-56e81f6f4512.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nDocker image: sigp/lighthouse:v2.0.1 \r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nThis metric always shows `1` despite the validator is not working.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nThis metric should show `0`\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nTurn off validator and after that check that metric in beacon node\r\n",
